      	<article allWordsNum="127">
            	<![CDATA[
Songkran (宋干节), the Thailand water festival, is the traditional Thai New Year. It runs for three days from April 13 to April 15 every year, and attracts many tourists from all over the world.
The water festival is about cleaning and fresh starts. During Songkran, splashing (泼) people with water can bring them good luck in the new year.
Do you know how to celebrate the Thailand water festival?
● Keep a good attitude! Both Thais and tourists are going to splash you with water—don’t get mad!
● Buy a water cannon (水炮) in the market, and then you can join the fun!
● The traditional way to wish someone well at Songkran and to make peace after splashing them is with: Sah-wah-dee pee mai. It means "Happy New Year!"
           	]]>
            </article>
